u want to feel the spend in real-time, run the dinner on debit instead.\n\n---\n\n## 2. "If I skip eating out for the rest of the month, where does that money actually go?"\n\n**A. FRAME:** Cycle behavior (next 14 days) translating into monthly savings + cash routing.\n\n**B. INPUTS:**\n- Dining logged April: $38.20 (one entry, 2026-04-07, Variable Spend Log)\n- Days elapsed in April: 23, dining events observed: 1 → ~1 event per ~3 weeks, OR if pattern is weekly and one was missed in logging, ~1/week\n- Days remaining in April: 7\n- Monthly Savings Estimate: $0.00 (Monthly Savings)\n- HYSA: $15,000.00 / target $15,000.00 — MET (HYSA gap $0)\n- Roth IRA: $0.00 — unfunded (Roth IRA)\n- 401(k): contributing 4%, capturing full 4% of 8% ceiling match — leaving $1,080/yr on the table (401(k) match gap)\n\n**C. CALCULATION:**\n\nDining run-rate, two scenarios:\n```\nConservative (1 event / 3 weeks):\n  Remaining April dining avoided    ~$0–$40\nRealistic (1 event / week, ~$38 avg):\n  2 events × $38                    ~$76\nAggressive (2 events / week):\n  4 events × $38                    ~$152\n\nWorking estimate: $60–$100 saved over the next 14 days.\n```\n\nWhere it actually lands:\n```\nStep 1: Spend doesn't happen on QuickSilver\n        → QuickSilver May statement is ~$60–$100 lower\n        → May checking debit is ~$60–$100 smaller\n        → May Safe to Spend is ~$60–$100 higher\n\nStep 2: That higher May Safe to Spend then gets...\n        ...re-absorbed by May discretionary unless swept.\n```\n\n**D. VERDICT:** $60–$100 over 14 days, and it does NOT become savings on its own — it becomes a smaller May QuickSilver bill, which then gets eaten by May spending unless you actively move it. The dollars need a destination.\n\n**E. RISK / CAVEAT:** With Monthly Savings at $0.00, you have no auto-sweep absorbing this. It will dissolve into next month's variable budget unless you act.\n\n**Priority destination per the playbook stack:** HYSA is met. The 401(k) match gap is